  "original_title": "\u0dbd\u0db6\u0db1 \u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dbb\u0dda\u0daf\u0dd3 \u0db1\u0dc0 \u0db6\u0dbd\u0dcf\u0db4\u0ddc\u0dbb\u0ddc\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4 \u0dc3\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dad \u0d85\u0dba\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A budget with new hopes next year",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Cabinet Spokesman, Minister of Transport, Highways and Mass Media, Dr. Bandula Gunawardena said that the government has planned to present a budget with changes and new hopes for next year.",
        "The minister said yesterday (22) that the Cabinet approved the preparation of the annual budget estimate for the year 2023, increasing the state income which is currently 9 percent of the GDP to 11.3 percent, reducing the state expenditure which is 18.9 percent to 18.1 percent, primary He stated that the goals of reducing the budget balance from minus 4 percent to minus 1 percent, and reducing the budget gap from minus 9.9 percent to minus 6.8 percent are expected from this budget.",
        "The minister said that under the state enterprise reform, the institutions that are currently making losses should be restructured. The minister also said that out of the government's tax revenue of 1,298 billion rupees last year, only 1,115 billion had to be paid for government employee salaries and pensions.",
        "The minister said that he has to pay more than 1,000 billion annually as loan interest and said that the income of the country is 400 crores and the expenditure is 1,000 crores, due to which he has to borrow 600 crores daily.",
        "The minister said this while addressing the press conference to inform the Cabinet decisions held today (23) at the Government Information Department.",
        "The Minister also stated that a proposal presented by President Ranil Wickremesinghe as the Minister of Finance, Economic Stabilization and National Policy was approved."
      ],
